---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Starting with DE in Scrabble"
  description="Best DE- words for Scrabble scoring. DE is one of the most productive prefixes with hundreds of valid words. Free Scrabble guide. Free, instant results."
  keywords="de words scrabble, words starting with de, de prefix scrabble, deploy scrabble, defend scrabble, scrabble de words list, short prefix words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Starting with DE in Scrabble",
    "description": "Best DE- words for Scrabble scoring with strategy for using this productive prefix to hit premium squares.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-20",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-starting-with-de" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many words starting with DE are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "DE is one of the most productive prefixes in Scrabble with over 1,000 valid words across TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. These range from 2 letters (DE itself is valid in SOWPODS only) to 15+ letters. The sheer volume makes DE one of the most important prefixes to know — you will encounter DE- opportunities in nearly every game." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best DE words for scoring in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The highest-scoring common DE words include DETOXIFY (22 points base), DEJECTED (19 points), and DECRYPT (15 points). For practical scoring, 7-letter DE bingos like DEFLECT (13+50), DELIGHT (12+50), and DEPOSIT (10+50) are most valuable because they earn the 50-point bingo bonus on common letter combinations." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can DE be played as a word by itself in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "DE is valid as a standalone 2-letter word in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words / international dictionary) but NOT in TWL (North American tournament dictionary). In SOWPODS, DE is defined as a preposition meaning 'of' or 'from'. It scores 3 points and is extremely useful for parallel plays and tight board positions." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Starting with DE in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-20">June 20, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        DE is arguably the most productive two-letter prefix in Scrabble. With over a thousand valid words, it attaches to almost anything — turning common root words into longer scoring opportunities. The beauty of DE is its flexibility: it only costs 2 tiles from your rack, leaving 5 tiles to form the root word. This guide focuses on the best 20–30 DE words for competitive Scrabble scoring, organized by length and strategic value.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,000+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid DE Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">22</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Score (7-letter)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Grid: Most Useful DE Words -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Best for Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEFLECT (7) · DEPOSIT (7) · DELIGHT (7) · DECRYPT (7) · DEFENCE (7)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Highest Scoring</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DETOXIFY (22) · DEJECTED (19) · DEFYING (15) · DEFRAYED (16) · DECRYPT (15)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📝 Most Common</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEFINE · DEFEND · DELIVER · DEMAND · DEPLOY · DESIGN · DEVELOP · DESTROY</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Easy to Build</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEAL · DEAR · DEBT · DECK · DEED · DEEP · DEER · DEMO · DENY · DESK</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DE Words by Length (3–6 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Short DE words are incredibly versatile. Many are common English words you already know, which makes them easy to spot during gameplay. These words fit tight spaces and set up future extensions.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">3–4 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEW (7) · DEX (11) · DEN (4) · DEL (4) · DEAL (5) · DEAR (5) · DEBT (7) · DECK (11) · DEED (6) · DEEP (7) · DEFT (8)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">5–6 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DECAL (8) · DECAY (11) · DECOY (11) · DECOR (8) · DELAY (9) · DELVE (9) · DEMON (8) · DEPOT (8) · DERBY (11) · DETOX (13) · DEVICE (12)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">DE only costs <span class="text-white font-medium">2 tiles (3 points)</span> as a prefix, but it unlocks hundreds of extensions. Compare this to TRANS (5 tiles) or UNDER (5 tiles) — DE leaves you 5 remaining tiles to form the root word, making bingos much more achievable.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo-Length DE Words (7 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Seven-letter DE words are where this prefix truly shines. With only 2 tiles committed to the prefix, you have 5 tiles for the root — giving you far more bingo combinations than longer prefixes. Tournament players memorize these religiously.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos (High Value)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEFLECT (13+50) · DELIGHT (12+50) · DEPOSIT (10+50) · DECRYPT (15+50) · DEFUNCT (13+50) · DEFYING (15+50)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos (Common)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEFENCE (13+50) · DELIVER (11+50) · DESERVE (11+50) · DESPAIR (10+50) · DESTINY (11+50) · DESTROY (11+50) · DETAILS (8+50) · DEVELOP (13+50)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DE Words (8+ Letters)</h2>

      <p>Longer DE words are commonly formed by extending existing plays. If LIGHT is on the board, adding DE in front creates DELIGHT. If FROST is there, DEFROST appears. These extension plays are the bread and butter of experienced competitors.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">8 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEBUGGED · DECAYING · DECEIVED · DECLARED · DECLINED · DEDUCTED · DEFECTED · DEFLATED · DEFORMED · DEGRADED · DEJECTED · DELAYING · DELIVERY</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">9+ Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DECORATED · DEDICATED · DEFENSIVE · DELIVERED · DEMOCRACY · DEPARTURE · DEPRESSED · DESCRIBED · DEVELOPED · DESTROYED · DETHRONED · DETERMINE</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Maximizing DE Prefix Power</h2>

      <p>DE is unique among Scrabble prefixes because of its extreme productivity — there are so many valid DE- words that you will almost always find a play. Here is how top players exploit this advantage.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front-hook aggressively:</span> DE is the ultimate front-hook prefix. Words like FEND→DEFEND, FROST→DEFROST, LIGHT→DELIGHT, CODE→DECODE, POSIT→DEPOSIT all work. Scan the board every turn for DE- front-hook opportunities — they appear more often than any other prefix.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use DE as a 2-letter parallel word:</span> In SOWPODS, DE is a valid 2-letter word. This means you can play a word parallel to an existing one, forming DE as a cross-word. This scores both your main word AND the 2-letter DE (3pts) — adding free points to every parallel play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Combine DE with high-value tiles:</span> Words like DEX (11pts for 3 letters), DETOX (13pts), and DEFYING (15pts) combine the DE prefix with high-scoring letters (X, Y, J, K). Prioritize DE words that include premium tiles for maximum base scores.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target DW/TW with short DE words:</span> Short DE words (DECK, DEBT, DEFT, DENY) are perfect for hitting premium squares in tight spaces. DECK on a DW square = 22 points for just 4 tiles. These small plays add up across a full game.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DE Words with Premium Letters</h2>

      <p>The most valuable DE words combine the prefix with high-point tiles. These are your go-to plays when you draw X, Z, J, K, or Q alongside D and E.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">DETOXIFY</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">22 points base · 8 letters · Uses X and Y</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The highest-scoring common DE word. On a Double Word square, DETOXIFY scores 44 points base — and as a bingo, that is 94 points in a single play. Keep D-E-T-O-X-I-F-Y in mind whenever you draw the X tile.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ DE + High-Value Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEX (11) · DETOX (13) · DEJECTED (19) · DEFYING (15) · DEXTERITY (20) · DEZINC (18) · DEJECT (16) · DEKKO (14)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Common But Low-Scoring</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEAL (5) · DEAN (5) · DEER (5) · DEMO (7) · DENIED (8) — valid but avoid when higher alternatives exist. Use these only for board position.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Dictionary Note</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">DE as a standalone 2-letter word is <span class="text-white font-medium">only valid in SOWPODS</span> (international). In TWL (North American), you need at least 3 letters: DEW, DEN, DEL, etc. Always verify your dictionary before playing DE alone.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-cheat-sheet/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Cheat Sheet: Essential Words Every Player Must Know</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/beginner-scrabble-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Beginner Scrabble Strategy: Tips to Win More Games</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-trans/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Starting with TRANS in Scrabble</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔍 Try these words in our free Scrabble solver — instant results, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
